Lists are used to store multiple items in a single variable.
Lists are created using square brackets:

list1=["apple","banana","cheery"]
list2=['1','2','3']
list3=["apple",'2',"banana"]
list4=["apple","banana","cheery","banana"]

print(list1)
print(list2)
print(list3)
print(list4)
print(len(list1))
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
Access Elements 
Indexing starts from 0 

print(list1[1])
print(list1[-1])
print(list1[1:2])
print(list1[1:])
print(list1[-2:-1])
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
Change List Elements

list1[1]="bloosom"
list1[1:5]='1','2','3','4','5'
list1.insert(2,"watermelon")
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
Add List Items
By using append and insert and extend methods 

list1.append("watermelon")
list1.insert(1,"kite")
list2=['1']
list1.extend(list2)
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
Remove List Items
By using remove and pop and delete and clear

list1.remove("banana")
list1.pop(2)
del list1
list1.clear()   # clear takes only one arguement
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
Sort List

list1=['3','5','1','4']
list1.sort()
list1.reverse()
list1.sort(key=str.lower)
print(list1)
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
Copy List
By using copy and list and slice method

list1=['3','5','1','4']
list2=list1.copy()
list2=list(list1)
list2=list1[:]
print(list2)
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
Join List
By extend method and by + opertor

list1=['3','5','1','4']
list2=["apple"]
list1=list1+list2
list1.extend(list2)
print(list1)
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
END OF FILE
